1. *Prolaze* sati, a ja nisam ni primetio. (Hours are passing, and I didn't even notice.)
2. Ova ulica je prepuna ljudi koji *prolaze*. (This street is full of people who are passing by.)
3. Moramo biti brzi ako ne želimo da nam prilika *prođe*. (We need to be quick if we don't want the opportunity to pass us by.)
4. Često *prolazim* ovim parkom na putu do posla. (I often pass through this park on my way to work.)
5. Lepota ovog pejzaža nikada neće *proći*. (The beauty of this landscape will never pass away.)
6. Sadašnji trenutak je jedino što imamo i nikada više se neće *prolaziti*. (The present moment is all we have and we will never pass through it again.)
7. Ponekad mi se čini da život brzo *prolazi*. (Sometimes it seems to me that life passes by quickly.)
8. Kada *prođeš* kroz teška iskustva, postaješ jači. (When you pass through difficult experiences, you become stronger.)
9. *Prođi* malo bliže, ne čujem dobro. (Come a little closer, I can't hear well.)
10. Ne mogu da verujem da je već *prošlo* tri meseca od našeg poslednjeg susreta. (I can't believe it's already been three months since our last meeting has passed.)